# Website deploy workflow

When you change anything under `apps/website/` (especially `index.html`):

1. **Finish the edit** — keep it a single-file static site; no build step required.
2. **Commit** only the website files (and related deploy docs if touched).
3. **Push to GitHub** on `main` (`origin`) so the live site stays in sync.

Do not leave website work local-only. Preview locally if helpful (`python3 -m http.server 8080 --directory apps/website`), but always push when the change is done.

If the user asked not to commit in the same message, finish the edit and remind them the site still needs a push.
